This is a strong point, while the IELTS score may not seem directly relevant to a software engineer role, it demonstrates a strong command of the English language. description: This is a weak point because, similar to the other projects, there are not enough technical details provided. While it mentions enhancing Tailored Discovery for TikTok shop and designing UI using Figma, the description is high-level. It lacks specific information about algorithms, data structures, or any challenging technical problems solved during the TechJam. To improve this, the candidate should elaborate on the technical aspects of the solution, such as how user preferences were extracted and how the dynamic theming was implemented.

description: This is a weak point because the description clearly states that it is 'A project from a tutorial video'. This indicates a lack of originality and independent problem-solving. While following tutorials is a good way to learn, it does not showcase the candidate's ability to tackle real-world problems. To improve this, the candidate should focus on highlighting original projects or contributions, even if they are small.

text: Bachelor of Science: Computer Science, Advanced
description: This is a weak point because the expected graduation date is June 2027. This indicates that the candidate is still a student and lacks significant professional experience. While the coursework is relevant, the lack of practical, full-time experience could be a concern for employers. To mitigate this, the candidate should focus on highlighting internships, personal projects, and contributions to open-source projects that demonstrate practical skills and experience. Since the job description requires a ton of practical experience the CV must address this concern.
